<paragraph id="E66EB3396E0DAD1C1EF19183522DC163" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">
<pageBreakToken id="D5D391A01309488FE6D1166FD3253D42" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" start="start">In</pageBreakToken>
describing 
<taxonomicName id="1A55581531DA4729AAA3AD6A29A4B74E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Penstemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Penstemon coloradoensis" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coloradoensis">
<emphasis id="36073BEDBF6511D17BE5B5A4C9B04E54" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Penstemon coloradoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E56B65A0DD4636197CCBC2E6CAEE4C80" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2478041" author="Nelson, A" journalOrPublisher="Club" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" pagination="350 - 358" refId="B4" refString="Nelson, A, 1899. New plants from Wyoming.-IX. Bull. Torrey Bot. Club 26: 350 - 358, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2478041" title="New plants from Wyoming. - IX. Bull. Torrey Bot." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2478041" volume="26" year="1899">Nelson (1899)</bibRefCitation>
stated &quot; 
<emphasis id="F88B5F12315DDD52E76C55D889ECB401" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">
I have before me specimens from two collections made near Mancos, Colo., by Messrs. Baker, Earle, and Tracy, 1898 and distributed as P. 
<taxonomicName id="7AB81457208D497CB497D05D257F2FC8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Penstemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="caespitosus" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caespitosus">caespitosus</taxonomicName>
Nutt. Also from two collections by Professor Crandall, from Hotchkiss, Colo., 1892, and from Durango, 1898, both distributed as P. 
<taxonomicName id="EDF5707B0B0F595AA8727C304DA9EA39" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Penstemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="linarioides" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linarioides">linarioides</taxonomicName>
Sileri Gray.
</emphasis>
&quot; 
<bibRefCitation id="72CD06D9C53BC5D063ECBF5E255CC63D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2478041" author="Nelson, A" journalOrPublisher="Club" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" pagination="350 - 358" refId="B4" refString="Nelson, A, 1899. New plants from Wyoming.-IX. Bull. Torrey Bot. Club 26: 350 - 358, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2478041" title="New plants from Wyoming. - IX. Bull. Torrey Bot." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2478041" volume="26" year="1899">Nelson (1899)</bibRefCitation>
did not designate a 
<typeStatus id="AFBB0B483BB385C04065A79D1473786F">holotype</typeStatus>
; the collections he cited are 
<typeStatus id="8447FEDB99B75E9CC41E73D555713178">syntypes</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="D3628E84E7F052F4553179034666F138" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2481121" author="Keck, DD" journalOrPublisher="Club" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" pagination="357 - 381" refId="B3" refString="Keck, DD, 1937. Studies in Penstemon IV. The section Ericopsis. Bull. Torrey Bot. Club 64: 357 - 381, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2481121" title="Studies in Penstemon IV. The section Ericopsis. Bull. Torrey Bot." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2481121" volume="64" year="1937">Keck (1937)</bibRefCitation>
designated C.F. Baker, F.S. Earle, and S.M. Tracy 70 (RM) as the 
<typeStatus id="EEC93A98573ACC9E43C2B12E7EAEE5DC">lectotype</typeStatus>
, of which there currently are two sheets, suggesting a second-step lectotypification might be necessary. Accession labels on the two sheets indicate they were received from the herbaria of F.S. Earle in 1899 (RM0004187; accession number 13703) and George E. Osterhout in 1938 (RM0004188; accession number 165282), subsequent to 
<normalizedToken id="E3B35BE5EBADB03BEDC440E7E2B6D964" originalValue="Keckâ€™s">Keck's</normalizedToken>
<typeStatus id="B05D419076F189359BE5A66CC544C981">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation. RM0004187 bears annotations by A. Nelson (
<taxonomicName id="83FB1C1C3BB5C1D00671A9C33522548B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Penstemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Penstemon coloradoensis" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coloradoensis">
<emphasis id="0845E84FD62F5873E07C21EF54763E61" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">Penstemon coloradoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A. N. n. sp., without date), F.W. Pennell (
<taxonomicName id="E01260F1E2066CDAAC198E2561FC1948" genus="P." lsidName="P. coloradoensis" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="coloradoensis">
<emphasis id="BA859F65DC07369C5F38A4B297DD3AA9" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">P. coloradoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, type, 1916), and D.D. Keck (
<taxonomicName id="1717CC4DF4E6393F6F7995891F786B09" genus="P." lsidName="P. linarioides subsp. coloradoensis" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" rank="subSpecies" species="linarioides" subSpecies="coloradoensis">P. linarioides A. Gray subsp. coloradoensis</taxonomicName>
(A. Nelson) D.D. Keck, type, 1936). RM0004188, the later accession, was not annotated by Nelson, Pennell, or Keck. Whether Nelson had another sheet at RM that was lost, destroyed, or sent elsewhere, or had access to a sheet from some other herbarium, is not known. Of the two sheets currently at RM, only RM0004187 appears to have been there when Nelson described 
<taxonomicName id="72CF6FD1B8704528EB3BBE746EC38BBC" genus="P." lsidName="P. coloradoensis" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="coloradoensis">
<emphasis id="657D9F2EC8B77748116E800C76BC9321" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="35">P. coloradoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and later seen by Keck when he lectotypified the name. RM0004187 is taken as the 
<typeStatus id="31C83CA59249EEE3207DB36B9DF04881">lectotype</typeStatus>
, 
<accessionNumber id="7F070C4C03D712B346A84DE706D75896" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/RM004188">RM004188</accessionNumber>
is taken as an isolectotype, and no second-step lectotypification is needed. As an aside, the sheet at KSC is 
<taxonomicName id="EB12164F0D37FC5DCC572ACB53D008A0" authority="A. Nelson var. crandallii" genus="P." lsidName="P. crandallii subsp. var. var. crandallii" pageId="2" pageNumber="35" rank="variety" species="crandallii" subSpecies="var." variety="crandallii">P. crandallii A. Nelson var. crandallii</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
